  "title": "Spot the Difference Horror Framework",
  "description": "A framework for building Observation Duty style games; a genre that combines horror and spot-the-difference.",
  "longDescription": "<p>Inventory System: <a href=\"https://www.unrealengine.com/marketplace/en-US/product/9242cca82d0e4fb98263b5b3294bfd17\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simple Drag and Drop Inventory System in Blueprints - UE Marketplace (unrealengine.com)</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Observation Toolbox is a framework for quickly prototyping &#34;I&#39;m on Observation Duty&#34; style games, where players try to survive until the morning by surveying security cameras and reporting anomalies.</p><p>Completely written in commented blueprints and built with clarity in mind. Developers can easily build upon and create levels with flexible base classes.</p><p>A simple demo map populated with a few example anomalies is included, along with editor utility actions and a comprehensive debugging widget.</p><p><br /></p><p>You can read a beginners friendly tutorial <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1uIurTCqfUXi3ZoqAo5BzAg7nkQYljXyW/view?usp&#61;sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">HERE</a>.</p>",
